 "executive_summary": "A TRAV12-2-encoded TCR specific for the MART-1-derived melanoma epitope ELAGIGILTV (ELA) presented by HLA-A*0201 was structurally characterized to explain why this TCR gene segment is used in >87% of CD8+ T cells targeting this dominant tumor antigen. The structure reveals that germ line-encoded regions of the TCR alpha chain dominate contacts with the peptide, an unusual \"innate\" pattern of antigen recognition that contrasts with typical CDR3-mediated engagement. This germ line-driven recognition mechanism accounts for the exceptional frequency and prevalence of TRAV12-2-based responses to MART-1 in the naive repertoire, with implications for understanding natural anti-tumor immunity and potentially cancer vaccine and TCR engineering strategies targeting this immunodominant epitope.",
